@da-woods Thanks for having a look at it.
I was surprised (after 5 month!) to see that `g` is allowed to have fused type arguments, while it seems forbidden for `f`.

Would a xfail test be welcome to make this behaviour more transparent?

> the table of function pointers mechanism isn't being generated correctly, or isn't being used

For what it's worth it looks like the table isn't being generated correctly

```
struct __pyx_vtabstruct_9fusedtest_B {
  struct __pyx_vtabstruct_9fusedtest_A __pyx_base;
  double (*__pyx_fuse_0f)(struct __pyx_obj_9fusedtest_B *, double);
};
```

It's generating a new, separate entry for `B.f` and instead of overwriting the entry for `A.f`.
